When I started as an editor at The Knot over six years ago, lab-grown diamond engagement rings were a glimmer on the radar of the jewelry industry. During my time covering wedding trends, I've witnessed their popularity surge firsthand. According to data from our 2024 Jewelry and Engagement Study, we found that over half of all engagement rings (52%, to be exact) featured a [lab-grown diamond](https://www.theknot.com/content/lab-grown-diamonds); a six percent increase from 2023. Our stats also found that the [average engagement ring cost](https://www.theknot.com/content/how-much-to-spend-on-engagement-ring) continues to fall, while the [average carat size](https://www.theknot.com/content/average-engagement-ring-carat-size) is slowly increasing. We can correlate this trend to the rise of lab-grown diamonds, which are generally less expensive than mined diamonds. 

Lab-grown diamond engagement rings aren't just a fad. Thanks to their often lower price point, they offer a budget-friendly option for couples to get their dream engagement ring without over-spending. Of course, if you're deciding between [different types of diamonds](https://www.theknot.com/content/types-of-diamonds) (like a lab-grown diamond or a mined stone), there are pros and cons to consider for both. Even though they're manufactured, lab-grown diamonds are chemically the same as mined diamonds. They tend to be less expensive than natural diamonds because the creation process is more efficient and cost-effective. Lab-grown diamonds don't have the same monetary value as natural diamonds over time, but if that doesn't matter to you, choosing one for your engagement ring can be a great choice, both in terms of cost and aesthetics.

## Where to Buy Lab Diamond Engagement Rings

Over the last few years, engagement rings with lab-created diamonds have become more popular and far more common. Many jewelry brands and retailers create and carry them, so they're no longer hard to find. That said, some brands specifically specialize in lab-created diamond jewelry. Below are several trustworthy online retailers that sell lab-grown diamond engagement rings. Alternatively, if you prefer to shop in person, use [The Knot Vendor Marketplace](https://www.theknot.com/marketplace/jewelers) to search for jewelers that sell lab-created diamond rings near you.

[**Blue Nile**](https://www.bluenile.com/?a_aid=5c3367062612e&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=TKEditorial&data1=TK-lab-grown-diamond-rings&utm_source=pap&utm_medium=affiliates): For 25 years, Blue Nile has been a go-to destination for wedding jewelry. While the brand has a showroom in New York City, you can easily shop for diamond and gemstone engagement rings on their website. The experience is totally customizable, allowing you to create your own design from scratch. Toggle between "natural" and "lab-grown" views to compare your diamond options. Or, you can also browse a collection of pre-designed rings. 

[**Charles & Colvard**](https://charlesandcolvard.sjv.io/c/64733/1375212/16476?subId1=Theknot.com-lab-grown-diamond-rings&u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.charlesandcolvard.com)**:** Charles & Colvard is known for moissanite engagement rings, but they also make equally beautiful lab-grown diamonds. On their website, you can expect to find a range of classic and traditional engagement ring options, each with some customizable elements. 

[**Jean Dousset**](https://www.pjatr.com/t/8-12864-88550-287526?sid=Theknot.com-lab-grown-diamond-rings&website=177979&url=https%3A%2F%2Fjeandousset.com)**:** As the great-great-grandson of Louis Cartier, Jean Dousset continues his family's legacy in the diamond industry…with a twist, that is. His eponymous brand offers only lab-grown diamond engagement rings and wedding bands and is beloved by celebrities like Paris Hilton, Amy Adams and Eva Longoria. 

[**Kay Jewelers**](https://www.dpbolvw.net/click-8213893-11554448?sid=Theknot.com-lab-grown-diamond-rings&url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kay.com)**:** You know how the saying goes: Every kiss begins with Kay. For over 100 years, this iconic diamond brand has been one of the most trusted names in the industry. Today, they offer both lab-grown and mined stones, and partnerships with luxury designers like Monique Lhuillier, Neil Lane and Le Vian blend high-end jewelry with accessible pricing. 

[**VRAI**](https://vraiandoro.qyov.net/c/64733/615401/10025?subId1=TK-lab-grown-diamond-rings&u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.vrai.com%2F): All of the lab-grown diamonds from VRAI are manufactured at the Diamond Foundry in San Francisco, California. By crystallizing greenhouse gas into rough diamond using zero-emission river energy, VRAI's jewelry requires no carbon offsets. What's more, their team of Belgian cutters includes one of the co-creators of the iconic princess-shaped diamond. Shop their pre-designed collection of engagement rings, or make your own unique piece with one of their loose lab-grown diamonds. 

[**Holden**](https://go.linkby.com/FDTFBPYQ): Holden's curation of gender neutral lab-grown diamond engagement rings are designed to look like modern heirlooms. Not only is the brand a Climate Label Certified company, they've been contributing to a net zero future since 2021. Inclusivity is a core value, as Holden donates 1% of all sales to The Trevor Project to provide LGBTQ youth with life-saving resources.

[**Mejuri**](https://mejuri.pxf.io/c/64733/890344/12305?subId1=Theknot.com-lab-grown-diamond-rings&u=https%3A%2F%2Fmejuri.com)**:** You may love Mejuri for their ultra-trendy croissant huggie earrings or dainty bracelets, but they sell lab-grown wedding bands too. This cool-girl retailer has a beautiful collection of diamond eternity stackers in all shapes, from rounds and ovals to pears and baguettes.

[**With Clarity**](https://www.awin1.com/cread.php?awinmid=89517&awinaffid=565019&campaign=&clickref=Theknot.com-lab-grown-diamond-rings&ued=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.withclarity.com&platform=pl)**:** At With Clarity, you'll find both natural and lab-grown diamonds. The jewelry brand is heavy on personalization and offers tons of customization options to create your dream ring. However, they also have a collection of ready-to-ship lab diamond engagement rings with moderate pricing. 

[**Grown Brilliance**](https://grownbrilliance.sjv.io/c/64733/1750582/20460?subId1=Theknot.com-lab-grown-diamond-rings&u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.grownbrilliance.com)**:** There are hundreds of lab-created diamond engagement rings available to shop at Grown Brilliance, and most of them are customizable. If ethical practices and sustainability are important to you, Grown Brilliance delivers. The diamonds are 100% conflict-free, they use 96% recycled gold and their packaging is made from 100% recyclable materials.

Taylor Custom Rings offers a wide variety of lab-created diamond engagement rings. These tend to be a little bit more on the unique side, with pieces that feel trendy and fresh. They also sell a lot of vintage-inspired rings that are particularly glamorous.

[**James Allen**](https://www.jamesallen.com/?a_aid=5c3367062612e&a_cid=dfef9309&chan=TKEditorial&data1=TK-lab-grown-diamond-rings)**:** For nearly 20 years, James Allen has been one of the most prestigious names in the jewelry industry. Their 360-degree virtual technology makes it easy to shop for an engagement ring from home if you can't make it into one of their brick-and-mortar showrooms. While you can easily shop pre-designed rings, they also offer loose lab-grown stones. Beyond traditional diamonds, they create fancy-colored diamonds too. 

[**Plum Diamonds**](https://plumdiamonds.pxf.io/c/64733/1963708/23974?subId1=Theknot.com-lab-grown-diamond-rings&u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.plumdiamonds.com): Not only does Plum Diamonds have an excellent [at-home engagement ring try-on kit](https://www.theknot.com/content/why-you-should-try-engagement-rings-on-before-you-buy), they offer wedding jewelry for every budget and style. Beyond classic solitaires, you can browse a catalogue of unique styles, including bypass bands and antique cluster settings. 

## Our Favorite Lab Diamond Engagement Rings

There are so many beautiful lab-created diamond engagement rings out there, and browsing through them to find the perfect proposal piece can feel overwhelming. We've curated a short list of editor-vetted lab-grown diamond engagement rings that you can shop right now. 

### Blue Nile Classic Simple Solitaire Engagement Ring

![Blue Nile Classic Simple Solitaire Engagement Ring](https://media-api.xogrp.com/images/818c5c10-132b-4d13-b98e-06c569a94217~rs_768.h-cr_0.0.1600.1600)

_Photo: Blue Nile_

According to our data, ovals are one of the [most popular engagement ring shapes](https://www.theknot.com/content/the-knot-engagement-ring-stats) right now. This timeless style from Blue Nile is as elegant as it is budget-friendly: Since the elongated shape of an oval can make it look larger than its actual carat size, you can opt for a "smaller" stone without sacrificing its sizable appearance. 

[From $650 | Blue Nile](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/classic-simple-solitaire-engagement-ring-in-14k-yellow-gold-item-203348?a_aid=5c3367062612e&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=TKEditorial&data1=TK-lab-grown-diamond-rings&utm_source=pap&utm_medium=affiliates)

### Jean Dousset Chelsea Solitaire Lab Diamond Engagement Ring

![Jean Dousset Chelsea Solitaire Lab Diamond Engagement Ring](https://media-api.xogrp.com/images/bd480cd2-5198-4245-88ec-c3ba30db7c17~rs_768.h-cr_0.0.3000.3000)

_Photo: Jean Dousset_

Emerald-shaped diamonds are the epitome of quiet luxury. But since their internal step-cut facets show inclusions more clearly than a traditional brilliant cut, mined emeralds come with a significantly higher cost. One way to get the look (à la Sofia Richie) is to opt for a lab-grown stone. The Chelsea solitaire from Jean Dousset is a beautiful option. Customize the metal setting to be the color of your choice, and if you aren't feeling the squared edges, replace it with another fancy shape like an oval, marquise, pear or cushion. 

[From $2,150 | Jean Dousset](https://www.pntrs.com/t/8-12864-88550-287526?sid=Theknot.com-lab-grown-diamond-rings&website=177979&url=https%3A%2F%2Fjeandousset.com%2Fproducts%2Fchelsea-solitaire-high-polish-lab-diamond-engagement-ring%3Fvariant%3D43864408129791%26)

### James Allen Oval-Cut Lab-Grown Diamond Petite Pavé Engagement Ring

![James Allen Oval-Cut Certified Lab-Grown Diamond Petite Pavé Engagement Ring](https://media-api.xogrp.com/images/2a729c35-280b-4acf-a9ae-087fded3a2fd~rs_768.h-cr_0.0.1600.1600)

_Photo: James Allen_

One of the best parts about buying a James Allen engagement ring is that you can customize the entire design from start to finish. However, if you'd rather browse pre-made styles, you have that option too. We love this ready-to-ship lab-grown diamond engagement ring, which highlights a beautiful oval center stone perched atop a sparkly pavé band. 

[From $1,820 | James Allen](https://www.jamesallen.com/engagement-rings/diamond-preset/oval-cut-1-ct-certified-lab-grown-diamond-petite-pave-engagement-ring-in-platinum-item-302518?a_aid=5c3367062612e&a_cid=dfef9309&chan=TKEditorial&data1=TK-lab-grown-diamond-rings&utm_source=pap&utm_medium=affiliates)

### Monique Lhuillier Bliss Marquise-Cut Lab-Grown Diamond Engagement Ring

![Monique Lhuillier Bliss Marquise-Cut Lab-Grown Diamond Engagement Ring](https://media-api.xogrp.com/images/33f213db-44e0-4e4e-8178-d3055b1edb3e~rs_768.h-cr_0.0.800.800)

_Photo: Kay Jewelers_

Monique Lhuillier doesn't just design wedding dresses. Through her exclusive partnership with Kay Jewelers, you can shop this designer's repertoire of whimsical engagement rings, all of which feature lab-grown diamonds. Most of Lhuillier's baubles feature romantic elements that mirror her iconic fashion designs, like this marquise-shaped center stone flanked by half moon and tapered baguette side stones. 

[$6,900 | Kay Jewelers](https://www.kqzyfj.com/click-8213893-11554448?sid=Theknot.com-lab-grown-diamond-rings&url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.kay.com%2Fmonique-lhuillier-bliss-marquisecut-labgrown-diamond-engagement-ring-212-ct-tw-18k-yellow-gold%2Fp%2FV-950303002)

### Taylor & Hart Lyra Engagement Ring

![Taylor & Hart Lyra Engagement Ring](https://media-api.xogrp.com/images/2e56e16a-af7c-4f09-9cf9-fad7528f7bf0~rs_768.h-cr_0.0.900.900)

_Photo: Taylor & Hart_

The Lyra ring is one of Taylor & Hart's top-ten most popular lab-grown diamond engagement rings, and it's not hard to see why. With a vintage-inspired floral burst halo, the design features an oval center stone surrounded by 14 smaller round diamonds. One of our favorite details is the fact that you can customize the signature gemstone on the inside of the band for a subtle pop of personalization that only you and the wearer will know about. 

[From $2,600 | Taylor & Hart](https://taylorandhart.com/us/engagement-rings/lyra-platinum-engagement-ring-oval-diamond)

### Plum Diamonds Three-Stone Trillion Ring

![Diamond engagement ring with gold band](https://media-api.xogrp.com/images/b74041b5-c373-471b-9bdc-b0f7ef8a1f6a~rs_768.h-cr_0.0.768.768)

It doesn't get much more classic and traditional than this lab-created diamond engagement ring. A round-shaped diamond sits on a sparkling, slim wedding band.
